{"title_page": "Rose Marie Compaor\u00e9", "text_new": "{{Expand French|Rose Marie Compaor\u00e9}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name            = Rose Marie Compaor\u00e9\n|native_name     = \n|image           = \n|caption         = \n|office          = 2nd Vice President of the [[National Assembly of Burkina Faso]]\n|term_start      = 30 December 2015\n|term_end        = 18 March 2020\n|predecessor     = \n|successor       = \n|birth_name      = \n|birth_date      = {{birth date|1958|11|13}}\n|birth_place     = [[Zoundw\u00e9ogo]]\n|death_date      = {{death date and age|2020|3|18|1958|11|13}}\n|death_place     = [[Ouagadougou]], [[Burkina Faso]]\n|spouse          = \n|children        = \n|party           = [[Union pour le Progr\u00e8s et le Changement|UPC]] \n|alma_mater      = \n|otherparty      = \n|education       = \n|occupation      = \n|website         = \n}}\n\n'''Rose Marie Compaor\u00e9''' (13 November 1958 \u2013 18 March 2020) was a Burkinab\u00e9 politician and member of the Union pour le Progr\u00e8s et le Changement (UPC) political party. She represented [[Zoundw\u00e9ogo Province]] in the National Assembly. Compaor\u00e9 served as the was the Second Vice President of the [[National Assembly of Burkina Faso]] from 30 December 2015 until her death from [[COVID-19]] on 18 March 2020.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200319-burkina-faso-sub-saharan-africa-coronavirus-covid19-death-who-tedros-adhanom-ghebreyesus|title=Burkina Faso reports Sub-Saharan Africa's first coronavirus death as WHO warns 'prepare for worst'|date=March 19, 2020|website=France 24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.africanews.com/2020/03/18/burkina-faso-s-first-covid-19-death-claims-top-lawmaker//|title=Burkina Faso's records first COVID-19 death in sub-Saharan Africa &#124; Africanews}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March 2020, she died at the age of 62 due to [[coronavirus disease 2019]] complications.<ref name=\"auto\"/> She was also a diabetic patient.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/topics/ce1qrvlelrrt/burkina-faso|title=Burkina Faso|website=BBC News}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Compaore, Rose Marie}}\n[[Category:1958 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Assembly of Burkina Faso\u200e]]\n[[Category:Burkinab\u00e9 women in politics]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Burkina Faso]]\n[[Category:Burkinab\u00e9 politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Centre-Sud Region]]\n\n{{BurkinaFaso-politician-stub}}\n\n[[fr:Rose Marie Compaor\u00e9]]\n", "text_old": "{{Expand French|Rose Marie Compaor\u00e9}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name            = Rose Marie Compaor\u00e9\n|native_name     = \n|image           = \n|caption         = \n|office          = 2nd Vice President of the [[National Assembly of Burkina Faso]]\n|term_start      = 30 December 2015\n|term_end        = 18 March 2020\n|predecessor     = \n|successor       = \n|birth_name      = \n|birth_date      = {{birth date|1958|11|13}}\n|birth_place     = [[Zoundw\u00e9ogo]]\n|death_date      = {{death date and age|2020|3|18|1958|11|13}}\n|death_place     = [[Ouagadougou]], [[Burkina Faso]]\n|spouse          = \n|children        = \n|party           = [[Union pour le Progr\u00e8s et le Changement|UPC]] \n|alma_mater      = \n|otherparty      = \n|education       = \n|occupation      = \n|website         = \n}}\n\n'''Rose Marie Compaor\u00e9''' (13 November 1958 \u2013 18 March 2020) was a Burkinab\u00e9 politician and member of the Union pour le Progr\u00e8s et le Changement (UPC) political party who represented [[Zoundw\u00e9ogo Province]] in the National Assembly. She served as the was the Second Vice President of the [[National Assembly of Burkina Faso]] from 30 December 2015 until her death from [[COVID-19]] on 18 March 2020.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.france24.com/en/20200319-burkina-faso-sub-saharan-africa-coronavirus-covid19-death-who-tedros-adhanom-ghebreyesus|title=Burkina Faso reports Sub-Saharan Africa's first coronavirus death as WHO warns 'prepare for worst'|date=March 19, 2020|website=France 24}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.africanews.com/2020/03/18/burkina-faso-s-first-covid-19-death-claims-top-lawmaker//|title=Burkina Faso's records first COVID-19 death in sub-Saharan Africa &#124; Africanews}}</ref>\n\nOn 18 March 2020, she died at the age of 62 due to [[coronavirus disease 2019]] complications.<ref name=\"auto\"/> She was also a diabetic patient.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/topics/ce1qrvlelrrt/burkina-faso|title=Burkina Faso|website=BBC News}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Compaore, Rose Marie}}\n[[Category:1958 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Members of the National Assembly of Burkina Faso\u200e]]\n[[Category:Burkinab\u00e9 women in politics]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Burkina Faso]]\n[[Category:Burkinab\u00e9 politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Centre-Sud Region]]\n\n{{BurkinaFaso-politician-stub}}\n\n[[fr:Rose Marie Compaor\u00e9]]\n", "name_user": "Scanlan", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rose_Marie_Compaor%C3%A9"}
